      7 
      انفجّت القَوْسُ, (A,) inf. n. اِنْفِجَاجٌ, (O,)
The bow had its string distant from its كَبِد [q. v.];
(A, O;) [and so, app., ↓ فَجَّت, for] ↓ فَجَجٌ, in a
bow, signifies the state of having the string distant
from the كَبِد thereof. (S, O.)


      مُفْرِخٌ A hen-bird having [or producing by
hatching] a young one [or young ones (see 2)];
(L, K;) as also ↓ مُفَرِّخٌ. (L.)


      فِرْشَةٌ Form; appearance; garb; or the like;
syn. هَيْئَةٌ: so in the saying, هُوَ حَسَنُ الفِرْشَةِ [He
is goodly in form, &c.]. (O, K.)


      فَرْعَنَةٌ Cunning; i. e. intelligence, or sagacity;
or intelligence mixed with craft and forecast;
(S, K, TA;) and pride, haughtiness, or insolence.
(TA.)


      فِرْنِدٌ i. q. أَبْزَارٌ [Seeds that are used in cooking,
for seasoning food; &c.]: pl. فَرَانِدُ. (IAar,
O, K.)


      فَصِيدَةٌ Dates kneaded and mixed with blood;
(Ibn-Kuthweh, O, L, K;) as also ↓ فُصْدَةٌ; (O,
K;) thus termed by Ibn-'Abbád: (O:) a medicine given to children. (Ibn-Kuthweh, O, L.)


      فُصْعَةٌ The prepuce of a boy, (IDrd, T, O, K,
TA,) when it is wide, so that the glans protrudes
from it, (IDrd, O, K, TA,) or when he withdraws it from over the glans, before he is circumcised. (T, TA.)


      فَيْلَجٌ [The cocoon of a silk-worm;] the thing
from which قَزّ is obtained: an arabicized word;
[from the Pers. پِيلَهْ pélah; but said to be] originally فَيْلَق, and thus some pronounce it. (Msb,)


      فَوَادٌ, (O, K,) with fet-h to the ف, (O,) like
سَحَاب [in form], (K,) i. q. فُؤَادٌ [generally meaning The heart (see other explanations in art. فأد)];
(O, K;) a dial. var. of the latter word. (O.)
